{"sequence":24,"timestamp":"2026-04-25T10:21:16.933270067Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-2f4bfd83","body":"finding_summary: The branch makes `## Nearby work` a required `bead_execution_prompt/1` section without a compatibility path for the older `/1` prompts that are already persisted on existing tasks. `BEAD_TASK_PROMPT_CONTRACT_VERSION` is still `1`, but `SECTION_NEARBY_WORK` was added to `BEAD_TASK_PROMPT_SECTION_TITLES` in `src/contexts/project_run_record/task_prompt_contract.rs:18-19,42-53`, and the renderer now always emits that section in `src/contexts/project_run_record/service.rs:1217-1231`. Older version-1 prompts generated before this bead therefore fail `validate_canonical_prompt_shape`, which disables canonical scope handling in `src/contexts/workflow_composition/review_classification.rs:519-521` and causes prompt-review / override validation to reject unchanged historical prompts in `src/contexts/workflow_composition/prompt_review.rs:328-339` and `src/contexts/project_run_record/service.rs:426-435`.\nremediation_hint: Either introduce a new contract version and keep consumers able to recognize/validate legacy v1 prompts, or keep `Nearby work` optional when validating older `/1` prompts.","dedup_key":"c01edfe147a20b107307abec5ce1c0edb061bb110bcdabed51aa793765ad8dbb","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260425091842","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
