{"sequence":44,"timestamp":"2026-04-25T11:06:42.266939792Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-2-f5738668","body":"finding_summary: `build_nearby_bead_context()` is treating hierarchy links as nearby dependency work. It passes the full `bead.dependencies` and `bead.dependents` arrays into `nearby_entries_from_relations()` (`src/cli/project.rs:2434-2437`), and that helper never filters by `DependencyKind` (`src/cli/project.rs:2457-2480`). Any bead with a `parent_child` link to its epic will therefore show that epic under `## Nearby work` as a direct dependency, and epics can likewise surface child beads as direct dependents. That misstates the relationship the section is supposed to convey and spends the nearby-context budget on hierarchy metadata instead of actual dependency/sibling context.\naffected_files: src/cli/project.rs:2434-2480\nremediation_hint: only include `DependencyKind::Blocks` edges in the direct dependency/dependent subsections; keep `parent_child` links for parent/sibling inference only.","dedup_key":"40fe080f9847ca590b09b05e72a04d698a37e3cde4e8199a8b0f8e312d3ca570","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260425091842","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":45,"timestamp":"2026-04-25T11:06:42.293779013Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-2-4a207ecd","body":"finding_summary: the new `## Nearby work` section is not actually preserved by canonical-prompt validation. `is_optional_canonical_section()` marks `Nearby work` optional for every `bead_execution_prompt/1` prompt (`src/contexts/project_run_record/task_prompt_contract.rs:55-58`), and `validate_canonical_prompt_shape()` therefore accepts prompts that omit it (`src/contexts/project_run_record/task_prompt_contract.rs:342-346` and `src/contexts/project_run_record/task_prompt_contract.rs:388-392`). Prompt-review drift detection relies on that validator (`src/contexts/workflow_composition/prompt_review.rs:328-339`), so a rewritten prompt can silently drop the new section and still be accepted as canonical. That makes the feature non-durable in normal workflows: the prompt starts with nearby context, then prompt review can remove it without any rejection.\naffected_files: src/contexts/project_run_record/task_prompt_contract.rs:55-58,342-346,388-392; src/contexts/workflow_composition/prompt_review.rs:328-339\nremediation_hint: either bump the contract version for the new shape or keep legacy compatibility in read-only consumers while requiring `## Nearby work` on newly generated/refined canonical prompts.","dedup_key":"ff6f4d8a33c29b65d67cf705c9386c6ea74e4f7f35225ce3f91fa3532974be6f","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260425091842","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
